			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I learned recently why the 2 finger salute is a vulgarity in Britain/France...a few weeks ago... been dying to tell someone ever since!
<br />

<br />
Once upon a time, it seems when the British were fighting the French... The French archers were greatly feared..
<br />

<br />
So when the British would come across an archer battle, they would not kill him, but used to cut off the two fingers used to draw a bow... so now that gesture is offensive...
<br />

<br />
Only reason I remember is that when Bush41 visited England in the early 90s, he gave the wrong "V" for victory sign... 
<br />

<br />

<br />
heehee<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=659115" target="_blank" class="postlink">Qintan FlurryofBlades (1)
