			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kelam,
<br />

<br />
You are close on why the V sign is a vulgarity in Enland but missing one point. It began as a taunt by the British to the French in battle. They would stick two fingers up as a V sign to upset the archers they were fighting. The premise here was the British showing off that they had those fingers, and that the French could expect to lose them when they were beaten. 
<br />

<br />
Also, I highly doubt the British feared the French, considering they kicked their asses. (Spot the Brit here.... hehe) <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
