<br />

<br />
In "civilized warfare" (oxymoron, by some standards?) a knight could be subdued for ransom back to his country or family.  Killing a knight was considered a heinous act.  The 'nobleman' should not be slain in battle.  In general about the only ones 'allowed' to attack a knight was an opposing knight.
<br />

<br />
The common footsoldier was generally not to touch a knight, because the footsoldier was 'beneath them' in society.
<br />

<br />
Archers would, at time, land an arrow upon a knight, usually this was chalked up to a mishap, although the offending archer could still face serious retribution over such an offense.
<br />

<br />
The knight, in many cases, would survive the arrow as it would fail to penetrate the ever thickening generations of armor.
<br />

<br />
The Crossbow, however, would be capable of piercing full plate armor.  In so doing, it would pierce the knight wearing the armor, which opened the knight up to all sorts of infections which could cause long term damage even should the knight survive the wound.
<br />

<br />
Oddly, I have the sneaking suspicion that the crossbow on earth, never achieved the damage dealing capabilities of an Elemental Bow in the hands of an EQ/AM3 Ranger with TS on Norrath. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=852643" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dharisk</a>
<br />
Ranger of Tunare (deity and server)</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
